</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="07AF96B5FFF5FFDBF52461AFFE72CEA7" pageId="17" pageNumber="252" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="4F0AC53EFFF5FFDBF52461AFFE72CEA7" blockId="17.[111,648,215,493]" pageId="17" pageNumber="252">PHENOLOGY. — Flowers have been collected in June and October, immature fruits in June.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="07AF96B5FFF5FFDBF5246201FEABCBC2" pageId="17" pageNumber="252" type="description">
<paragraph id="4F0AC53EFFF5FFDBF5246201FEC9CD66" blockId="17.[112,649,533,1161]" box="[113,258,533,559]" pageId="17" pageNumber="252">DESCRIPTION</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4F0AC53EFFF5FFDBF5246220FEABCBC2" blockId="17.[112,649,533,1161]" pageId="17" pageNumber="252">
Shrub, 
<quantity id="884D68DBFFF5FFDBF5966220FEEBCD04" box="[195,288,564,591]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="17" pageNumber="252" unit="m" value="1.25" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="0.5">
0.5- 
<specimenCount id="59B30EB7FFF5FFDBF5A56220FEEBCD04" box="[240,288,564,591]" pageId="17" pageNumber="252" type="generic">2 m</specimenCount>
</quantity>
. Twigs terete, glabrous; terminal buds glabrous. Leaves 3-5.5 × 
<quantity id="884D68DBFFF5FFDBF4E16240FDD2CD24" box="[436,537,596,623]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="17" pageNumber="252" unit="cm" value="1.75" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.5">1.5-2 cm</quantity>
, glabrous, stiffly chartaceous, elliptic, the base and apex obtuse, venation immersed on the upper surface, reticulation finely raised on the lower surface, lower surface finely and minutely gland-dotted, domatia absent, lateral veins difficult to discern, 4-6 on each side. Inflorescences 
<quantity id="884D68DBFFF5FFDBF4BA6306FD89CC66" box="[495,578,786,813]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="252" unit="cm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2-3 cm</quantity>
long, in the axils of bracts, racemose. Flowers 
<quantity id="884D68DBFFF5FFDBF7176326FD4DCC07" box="[578,646,818,844]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="252" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 mm</quantity>
in diameter, white, tepals half-erect at anthesis; tepals 
<quantity id="884D68DBFFF5FFDBF5E26365FEEDCCC7" box="[183,294,881,908]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="252" unit="mm" value="1.25" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.0">1-1.5 mm</quantity>
long, glabrous outside, sparsely pubescent inside; stamens 9, all 4-celled, glabrous, 
<quantity id="884D68DBFFF5FFDBF59463A5FECDCC80" box="[193,262,945,971]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="252" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
long; inner three stamens with 2 large glands at the base, the glands half as long as the stamens; staminodia not seen; pistil 
<emphasis id="7DC1192CFFF5FFDBF77863E5FDF5CB41" box="[557,574,1009,1034]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="252">c.</emphasis>
<quantity id="884D68DBFFF5FFDBF71063E4FD4DCB41" box="[581,646,1008,1034]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="252" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
long, glabrous, the style half as long as the ovary; receptacle cup-shaped, glabrous inside. Cupule cup-shaped, 
<quantity id="884D68DBFFF5FFDBF457645BFE8ECB22" box="[258,325,1103,1130]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="252" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
wide, 
<quantity id="884D68DBFFF5FFDBF4C4645BFE1FCB22" box="[401,468,1103,1129]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="252" unit="mm" value="8.0">8 mm</quantity>
high, fruit (immature) 
<emphasis id="7DC1192CFFF5FFDBF584647BFF29CBC3" box="[209,226,1135,1160]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="252">c.</emphasis>
7 × 
<quantity id="884D68DBFFF5FFDBF440647BFE90CBC2" box="[277,347,1135,1161]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="252" unit="mm" value="8.0">8 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="07AF96B5FFF5FFDBF52464BAFDE2C9EF" pageId="17" pageNumber="252" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4F0AC53EFFF5FFDBF52464BAFF1ECB8D" blockId="17.[113,647,1198,1700]" box="[113,213,1198,1224]" pageId="17" pageNumber="252">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4F0AC53EFFF5FFDBF52464DAFDE2C9EF" blockId="17.[113,647,1198,1700]" pageId="17" pageNumber="252">
<taxonomicName id="88B5BEBDFFF5FFDBF52464DAFEF7CBAC" authority="Werff, 2013" authorityName="van der Werff" authorityYear="2013" box="[113,316,1229,1256]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Ocotea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="17" pageNumber="252" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glaberrima" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="7DC1192CFFF5FFDBF52464DAFEF7CBAC" box="[113,316,1229,1256]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="252">Ocotea glaberrima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="66F2A457FFF5FFDBF41064DAFE56CBA3" box="[325,413,1230,1256]" pageId="17" pageNumber="252" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is an inconspicuous shrub. It stands out among the entirely glabrous 
<taxonomicName id="88B5BEBDFFF5FFDBF5E86519FEAFCA6C" box="[189,356,1293,1319]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Ocotea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="17" pageNumber="252" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="7DC1192CFFF5FFDBF5E86519FEC1CA6C" box="[189,266,1293,1319]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="252">Ocotea</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="37A285AEFFF5FFDBF4E76519FDF0CA6C" box="[434,571,1293,1319]" name="Madagascar" pageId="17" pageNumber="252">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
by its small leaves with an obtuse base and apex. The other glabrous species differ as follows: 
<taxonomicName id="88B5BEBDFFF5FFDBF76E6559FE09CACD" authority="van der Werff" authorityName="van der Werff" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Ocotea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="17" pageNumber="252" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="longipedicellata">
<emphasis id="7DC1192CFFF5FFDBF76E6559FED0CACD" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="252">Ocotea longipedicellata</emphasis>
van der Werff
</taxonomicName>
has flowers with a pedicel of 
<quantity id="884D68DBFFF5FFDBF45F6598FE80CAED" box="[266,331,1420,1446]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="252" unit="cm" value="1.0">1 cm</quantity>
; pedicels in 
<taxonomicName id="88B5BEBDFFF5FFDBF4B16598FD4DCAED" authority="Werff, 2013" authorityName="van der Werff" authorityYear="2013" box="[484,646,1420,1446]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Ocotea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="17" pageNumber="252" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glaberrima" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="7DC1192CFFF5FFDBF4B16598FD4DCAED" box="[484,646,1420,1446]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="252">O. glaberrima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="66F2A457FFF5FFDBF52465B8FF07CA8D" box="[113,204,1452,1478]" pageId="17" pageNumber="252" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
are 
<quantity id="884D68DBFFF5FFDBF45465BFFE83CA8D" box="[257,328,1451,1478]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="252" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
long; 
<taxonomicName id="88B5BEBDFFF5FFDBF4C265B8FED8CAAE" authority="van der Werff" authorityName="van der Werff" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Ocotea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="17" pageNumber="252" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sambiranensis">
<emphasis id="7DC1192CFFF5FFDBF4C265B8FD4CCA8E" box="[407,647,1451,1478]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="252">Ocotea sambiranensis</emphasis>
van der Werff
</taxonomicName>
has larger leaves with an acute apex and raised reticulation on both surfaces of the leaves; 
<taxonomicName id="88B5BEBDFFF5FFDBF440661FFE7DC96F" authority="Werff, 2013" authorityName="van der Werff" authorityYear="2013" box="[277,438,1546,1573]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Ocotea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="17" pageNumber="252" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glaberrima" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="7DC1192CFFF5FFDBF440661FFE7DC96F" box="[277,438,1546,1573]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="252">O. glaberrima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="66F2A457FFF5FFDBF495661FFDD0C96E" box="[448,539,1547,1573]" pageId="17" pageNumber="252" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
has only raised reticulation on the lower surface and 
<taxonomicName id="88B5BEBDFFF5FFDBF524665EFE85C92F" box="[113,334,1610,1636]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Mespilodaphne" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="17" pageNumber="252" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="madagascariensis">
<emphasis id="7DC1192CFFF5FFDBF524665EFE85C92F" box="[113,334,1610,1636]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="252">O. madagascariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is poorly known, but it has large leaves and is a large tree, in contrast with the small size of 
<taxonomicName id="88B5BEBDFFF5FFDBF47A669DFE01C9E8" authority="Werff, 2013" authorityName="van der Werff" authorityYear="2013" box="[303,458,1673,1699]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Ocotea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="17" pageNumber="252" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glaberrima" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="7DC1192CFFF5FFDBF47A669DFE01C9E8" box="[303,458,1673,1699]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="252">O. glaberrima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="66F2A457FFF5FFDBF487669EFDE2C9EF" box="[466,553,1674,1700]" pageId="17" pageNumber="252" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
